@davidhicks980 You accidentally sent me down quite the rabbit hole.

As it stands (`Flutter 3.24.0-1.0.pre.505 • channel master • Framework • revision 64b373b1f2 (15 minutes ago) • 2024-08-08 01:39:24 +0200`):
1. tab does not work (as Huy mentioned)
2. the arrow keys *do* work as expected, so long as the `MenuAnchor.menuStyle` is not padded.
3. Losing focus of the `MenuAnchor` does not close its menu still (this is tangential, but I figured I'd mention it as I haven't found a way to do this manually)

Per 2, the padding seems to prevent the first item from receiving focus, as in the example below.  Interestingly, the second item will receive focus next (unlike my production app, in which focus never makes it into the menu). 

Here is the code I've ripped out of our project, hopefully you can reproduce:

```dart
