If you're using blanket touch event prevention like ontouchstart="event.preventDefault()" to fix double-selection issues but finding that it breaks virtual keyboard activation on iOS/mobile, here's a targeted solution:

Problem: Global preventDefault() on touch events blocks ALL touch handling, including the touches needed to activate virtual keyboards on mobile devices.

Solution: Only prevent touch events on non-editable elements while allowing them on inputs/textareas:
```
  <script>
    document.addEventListener('touchstart', function(e) {
      if (!isEditableElement(e.target)) {
        e.preventDefault();
      }
    }, { passive: false });

    document.addEventListener('touchend', function(e) {
      if (!isEditableElement(e.target)) {
        e.preventDefault();
      }
    }, { passive: false });

    function isEditableElement(element) {
      const tagName = element.tagName.toLowerCase();
      const contentEditable = element.contentEditable;
      const isInput = tagName === 'input' || tagName === 'textarea';
      const isEditable = contentEditable === 'true' || contentEditable === '';
      return isInput || isEditable || element.closest('[contenteditable="true"]');
    }
  </script>
```
  - { passive: false } is required for preventDefault() to work in addEventListener() touch events
  - This preserves double-selection prevention on non-editable elements
  - Allows normal touch behavior on inputs/textareas so mobile keyboards can activate
  - Works with regular inputs, textareas, and contenteditable elements

> [@justinmc[<img alt="" width="15" height="15" src="chrome-extension://dlebflppeeemcdpidccbiblndppbmjmh/ospo-chrome-ext-logo.png">](https://teams.googleplex.com/jmccandless@google.com)](https://github.com/justinmc) Looks like this bug existed before any of my recent scrolling changes. It looks like the culprit is that we are trying to bring the selection into view when the selection changes.
> 
> [flutter/packages/flutter/lib/src/widgets/editable_text.dart](https://github.com/flutter/flutter/blob/ba393198430278b6595976de84fe170f553cc728/packages/flutter/lib/src/widgets/editable_text.dart#L3899-L3905)
> 
> Lines 3899 to 3905 in [ba39319](/flutter/flutter/commit/ba393198430278b6595976de84fe170f553cc728)
> 
>  if (selectionChanged || 
>      (userInteraction && 
>      (cause == SelectionChangedCause.longPress || 
>       cause == SelectionChangedCause.keyboard))) { 
>    _handleSelectionChanged(_value.selection, cause); 
>    _bringIntoViewBySelectionState(oldTextSelection, value.selection, cause); 
>  } 
> I think we can just avoid bringing the selection into view when the selection changes as a result of a handle drag. We can assume that if the selection was moved as a result of a handle drag, that the selection is already in view.

