As a follow-up, to fix the issue, I could wrap the widgets to override the shortcuts as so:


<details>
<summary>code sample</summary>

```dart
//@dart=2.12

import 'package:flutter/foundation.dart';
import 'package:flutter/material.dart';
import 'package:flutter/services.dart';

void main() async {
  runApp(
    MaterialApp(
      home: TextEditingShortcutsOverride(
        child: Material(child: TextFieldTest()),
      ),
    ),
  );
}

class TextFieldTest extends StatelessWidget {
  @override
  Widget build(BuildContext context) {
    return const TextField(
      minLines: 1,
      maxLines: 12,
      style: TextStyle(fontSize: 14),
    );
  }
}

class TextEditingShortcutsOverride extends StatelessWidget {
  TextEditingShortcutsOverride({required this.child});
  final Widget child;

  @override
  Widget build(BuildContext context) {
    if (kIsWeb)
      return Shortcuts(child: child, shortcuts: _webShortcutsOverride);
    else
      return child;
  }

  static final Map<LogicalKeySet, Intent> _webShortcutsOverride =
      <LogicalKeySet, Intent>{
    LogicalKeySet(LogicalKeyboardKey.arrowDown):
        const MoveSelectionDownTextIntent(),
    LogicalKeySet(LogicalKeyboardKey.arrowUp):
        const MoveSelectionUpTextIntent(),
  };
}
```
</details>



This is the workaround we'll use in our app for now. Removing `TextEditingShortcutsOverride` exposes the bug.

Maybe leveraging `TapRegion/TextFieldTapRegion` in `SelectableText` and `SelectableArea` may be the way forward to solve this issue wrt those widgets. I tried adding `TextFieldTapRegion` to `SelectableText` since internally it uses `EditableText` and using the `onTapOutside` callback and doing `focusNode.unfocus()` almost solved the issue (hides the selection overlay and hnaldes). However we don't have access to the `TextEditingController` that `SelectableText` uses so there is no way to clear the selection programmatically afaik.

With `TextField` this behavior can be accomplished with the following and the selection is cleared as well.

```dart
  child: TextField(
    focusNode: node,
    onTapOutside: (PointerDownEvent event) {
      node.unfocus();
    },
  ),
```

