Hi guys, I think I found the problem!

TLDR: `bool get _shouldCreateInputConnection => kIsWeb || !widget.readOnly;` in 
`editable_text.dart`. I changed this to always be `true` and it fixed both:
- enables Edit -> Copy and Edit -> Select All (but also enables Cut, Paste, etc. as well as typing into the field -- moves the cursor but does not type characters -- so just simply setting `_shouldCreateInputConnection` to `true` is not the solution);
- triggers `onFieldSubmitted` when I press Enter/Return on the `readOnly` field.

So it appears `TextInputConnection` is critical to these types of functions.

There's an **accessibility** issue that seems related to this one: on macOS desktop, the Edit menu bar -> **Copy** and **Select All** entries are not enabled when a `readOnly` text input is focused / selected. This is a problem because my custom screen readers send a ⌘-C (macOS) or `xsel` (Linux -- haven't tested yet) to get the current selected text and read it aloud. (My only workaround would be to enclose each field in ⌘-C shortcut.) Nonetheless, it's bad, because the menu bar behavior is inconsistent / unavailable only because of `readOnly`.

I drilled down to `TextEditable` and found that, when `readOnly` is true, a `TextInputConnection` is not created on desktop.

Here's relevant code in `editable_text.dart` (line ~2307):
```dart
  /// Whether to create an input connection with the platform for text editing
  /// or not.
  ///
  /// Read-only input fields do not need a connection with the platform since
  /// there's no need for text editing capabilities (e.g. virtual keyboard).
  ///
  /// On the web, we always need a connection because we want some browser
  /// functionalities to continue to work on read-only input fields like:
  ///
  /// - Relevant context menu.
  /// - cmd/ctrl+c shortcut to copy.
  /// - cmd/ctrl+a to select all.
  /// - Changing the selection using a physical keyboard.
  bool get _shouldCreateInputConnection => kIsWeb || !widget.readOnly;
```

It might be tricky to change this behavior because `TextField.onSubmitted` is coupled to the editing lifecycle ([from the documentation](https://api.flutter.dev/flutter/material/TextField/onSubmitted.html):  "Called when the user indicates that they are done editing the text in the field.").

Maybe overriding the enter key shortcut could help for this use case:

